Bungoma governor hopeful Stephen Mutoro has ditched Ford Kenya for ANC, citing frustration.In a statement to newsrooms on Wednesday, Mutoro said he made the decision after consulting supporters.&lsquo;&rsquo;I am delighted to be in a party headed by diplomat, nationalist, and senior politician from the Mulembe nation Musalia Mudavadi,&rsquo;&rsquo; he said.Mutoro, the Consumer Federation of Kenya chief, said he has not had second thoughts about the move. He had paid the nominations fees in Ford Kenya.&lsquo;&rsquo;I have been frustrated in Ford Kenya. There is no respect for the chain of command and preferred candidates are endorsed,&rdquo; he said.